comment_text:
I have to admit, I don't quite understand why Belift Lab chose to change ILLIT's concept so quickly. I thought "Magnetic" was their best work. I remember Belift Lab said their original concept was a "cute princess" style. This involved using ruching and frilled hems, playful, doll-like puffy skirts, and delicate fabrics like lace and chiffon to create a dreamy look, with just a touch of casual streetwear. So I have to ask why, after such a short time, did they suddenly shift from that cute look to an edgy, chic comeback style? Also, why did they go from bouncy, upbeat pop songs to a minimalist reggae-pop song?

In my opinion, the shift is too quick. It's only a semi-shift where they are still teasing a bright smile, then suddenly turn all chic and cool. The thing is, I feel they really fit the cute princess style better. They are still young, and "Magnetic" was definitely catchier.
